			<tr>
				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Not sure what role I'm supposed to be filling<a name="57074"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Aug 17 04 9:19 AM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>I've only been playing EverQuest for about two months.  I have a 56 Bard.  It's the only character type I have played.
<br />

<br />
I have enjoyed being a Bard up until this point, but I have a problem.
<br />

<br />
At this point, critters that con as dark blue to me are too dangerous to take on by myself.  Yeah, I can kite, but if I mess up even a little, I'm dead.  I can spend a couple hours kiting things to death, and lose everything I have gained if I miss a note at the wrong time and Selo drops.
<br />

<br />
In a group, I'm not much use.  That is really starting to bother me.  I do *pitiful* DPS.  My party enhancement songs are entirely eclipsed by spells other classes get.  People don't even want the mana song much unless they run out of KEI.
<br />

<br />
There must be something I can do that would make me a useful and valued member of a group, but I'm having no luck figuring out what it is.
<br />

<br />
</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
