			<tr>
				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: Not sure what role I'm supposed to be filling<a name="57077"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Aug 17 04 10:06 AM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>Aye, LDoN is a good place for you, you are in the heck levels right now, when nothing's going for you but your skill.  Use it. Learn to pull, it's tricky at first but get a CHA buff and learn to use a combination of lull and a distance pull song of your choice (low aggro, non DoT, such as cancel magic).  Also, learn to use your mez and charm songs to the benefit of the group, filling in for chanters on crowd control. Learn to twist in mez with your standard battle twist, toggling between monsters.  Again it's tricky, but with practice you will become a great bard and folks will completely forget your (all of our) lack of melee DPS.
<br />

<br />
As for songs not being great, when haste fades, and the haster's lom, mention that you've been playing near comparable haste all mission long, as backup and for the other benefits that stack.
<br />

<br />
Lastly, as for manasong, just mention that it stacks with KEI and they'll want you to play it constantly... hehe.
<br />

<br />
GL and yeah, soloing (other than swarm kiting or AoE kiting) at your level is near impossible and horrible exp.  Groups are fun, do your jobs well and you'll make friends fast...
<br />

<br />
Sinfonian</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
