			<tr>
				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: Not sure what role I'm supposed to be filling<a name="57084"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Aug 17 04 10:19 AM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>I am amazed you got to 56 before realizing you could not solo blues without kiting them. I was level 35 when I gave up trying to &quot;beat em down&quot;. But that was almost three years ago now.
<br />

<br />
What you add to a group is pulling power, overhaste, and mana song. You CAN do many other things but that is where what we do that is unique (well pulling is not unique but you get my point.)
<br />

<br />
Pull LDONs, you will hone your skills there and make a name for yourself. I did ldons for a long time. One day I was in one of the FEW raids I have ever been on and the monk was having a heck of a time splitting three mobs (before they had lull). He would pull.. FD and they would all walk away together. Finally I asked if I could give it a try, I lulled the three of them and hit the one we wanted with slow song. Poof a single pull in about 9 seconds.
<br />

<br />
Also don't be afraid to pre-mezz. The chanters will love you if you mezz any add so they can have time to get off their much longer mezz. Our mezz does not over write theirs so there is no danger.
<br />

<br />
Get Run3... you should be able to chant and swarm kite without having to use selo's. I made 10 levels in Nadox swarm kiting, that is an indoor zone and all I had was run3. PoD is the same thing.</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
