			<tr>
				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: Not sure what role I'm supposed to be filling<a name="57097"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Aug 17 04 11:10 AM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>Unless you group with regulars, its hard for a lot of people to see that actual benefits that bards are bringing to the tables. A warrior can see how much damage he is doing, a cleric can see how much she is healing, and a necro can see how much damage they are doing.
<br />

<br />
What the warrior doesn't see is how much more damage they are doing because you hasted them and boosted their strength, or how much faster the mob is dropping because you reduced its AC and put a damage shield on your tank.
<br />

<br />
What the cleric doesn't see is how much less she is having to heal because you buffed the armor class of the tank and slowed the mob.
<br />

<br />
What the necro doesn't see is how much more often her poison dots are landing because you debuffed the resist of the incoming mob.
<br />

<br />
Bards can do amazing things that the group will rarely, if ever, notice. When I see a room full of mobs and I know one of them is a caster, then I pull with my song that cancels magic. After the mob gets back to the group and has been engaged for a few ticks, you think anyone knows that the mob has had all of its buffs and damage shields removed? Doubtful.
<br />

<br />
What about when I tell the group to move up in the dungeon? You think any of them notice the trap that they just walked over that I disarmed, preventing them from being Dotted or damaged for 100+ points? Doubtful.
<br />

<br />
How about when that mob starts trying to complete heal or gate? Hardly anyone ever notices that you were chain mezzing, preventing the group from having to kill the same mob 3 or 4 times until its mana runs out.
<br />

<br />
Theres only 2 skills that the large majority of players recognize in a bard. One is the fact that they can play a mana song. The other is the fact that we can pull very fast and very well. All of our other benefits go mostly unnoticed by the group, you just have to take comfort in the fact that you KNOW the group is performing a lot better than they would if you were not there, even if they don't see it.
<br />

<br />
</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
