				<td colspan="2"><span>First of you need to change your attitude about yourself .   If you believe that you dont bring much you wont be convincing many groups.    You are a bard and you are a great class that bring alot of stuff to the table.
<br />

<br />
First you have battlecry of the vah'shir wich is a 15% overhaste .  This gives a nice dps boost , rogues and ranger loves this .  Even if they dont know what it is doesnt mean they dont get great benefit from it .   Educate them ,  tell them you are giving them a extra 15% haste that break the haste limit !  
<br />

<br />
Second you just got cantata of replenishement a level ago , this is a great regen song and mana regen that stack with KEI .  No self respecting caster will believe he has already enough mana regen ,  why do you think caster pay so much for FT items , cause they crave mana regen , they cannot live without it .  You bring in a additionnal 15 mana/ tick that freaking huge for a caster .  
<br />

<br />
You can mez stuff ,  you just got a 55 mez that can mez alot of stuff .   pratice holding 3-4 mobs , pratice locking mob down fast .   I have the time to lock down 3 mobs by the tmie a chanter mezzed one cause they dont have to be constantly re-targeting mobs wich make our targetting skill much superior to any standard chanter.  
<br />

<br />
Your melee may not be the greatest but it still theyre , do you see a chanter doing any sustained dps ? Nope you dont , in many case (with KEI buyable in pok) you are clearly superior to a chanter , you bring more to the table then them .  
<br />

<br />
Take pride in your class and dont get down because a newb who dont understand the greatness of a bard tell you otherwise .
<br />

