				<td colspan="2"><span>Wow,
<br />

<br />
I just don't get this... What level was this bard 2 months ago when you started playing him?  If you levelled a bard to 56 in 2 months you either should have been kickin butt or been PLed to an incredible degree.  If you were kickin butt, you shouldn't have these questions, I would think.  That leaves me to one of 3 hypotheses:
<br />
1. You picked up this bard from someone else...so you are missing some skills...
<br />
2. You were incredibly PLed and/or twinked... so you are missing some skills...
<br />
3. You kicked butt as a bard for 2 months and had a recent brain injury...
<br />

<br />
To your points:
<br />
<blockquote><b>Quote:</b><br><span class="quote">At this point, critters that con as dark blue to me are too dangerous to take on by myself. Yeah, I can kite, but if I mess up even a little, I'm dead. I can spend a couple hours kiting things to death, and lose everything I have gained if I miss a note at the wrong time and Selo drops</span></blockquote>
<br />
Uh... yes and no... toe to toe, solo... yeah anything dark blue is gonna rip your arm off and beat you with the bloody stump.  This is true for almost every class.  But at 56, bard soloing can be AWESOME... which begs the question... If you can lose 2 hours of work in one death... how are you kiting, and where?  And do you know about rezzes?  At 56 I was swarming the stalkers in PON whenever I could.  I was PLing friends doing it sometimes and the XPs and loot were awesome.  Or if I wanted to solo and stalkers were camped, I would do flies in POD where the XPs were nice and the loot sucked eggs.
<br />

<br />
Your comments make me think you are aiming at AoE kiting though.  I could be wrong, but its that &quot;one little mistake&quot; thing that makes me think that.  AoE kiting is tough, no doubt, it can be rewarding XP wise but it can be frustrating too.
<br />

<br />
But even 1-on-1 charm kiting or chant kiting is passable XPs at this level (though not if you are accustomed to the pace of the others)
<br />

<br />
OK enough on solo.. on to grouping issues:
<br />
<blockquote><b>Quote:</b><br><span class="quote">In a group, I'm not much use. That is really starting to bother me. 
<br />
</span></blockquote>
<br />
HUH?!?!?!?
<br />
What class are we talking about again?  Not a bard right?  What kinda uber group is this?
<br />
<blockquote><b>Quote:</b><br><span class="quote">I do *pitiful* DPS. </span></blockquote>
<br />
Melee DPS, just yours, I guess you could say that.. its not unimportant DPS, depending on group makeup,  but its not your main function either.  But lets suppose the group has ALL the bases covered without you... All they need from you is DPS, they think...Mem those chants and see if the tank can keep the aggro... make it easier for him by throwing in the over-the-cap haste and mana song too, but shhh don't tell.  Your DPS equals your personal DPS plus the added DPS the group does because you are here, and that shouldn't be pathetic, you just arent giving yourself credit.
<br />
<blockquote><b>Quote:</b><br><span class="quote">My party enhancement songs are entirely eclipsed by spells other classes get.</span></blockquote>
<br />
This is true and untrue.  Chorus of Celerity is eclipsed by shaman and enchanter hastes, but thats OK.  SOW ain't got nothin on us.  Nothing in the game competes with our over-the-cap haste.  And our role is primarily to find and fill whatever gaps are present in the current group... no haster.. bards on it... no slower.. bards on it... need snare.. bards got it... need crowd control.. bards your man...need resists... nothin like a bard for resists... need a puller... step aside, bard comin thru... inc %T.  
<br />

<br />
In group situations, I am most often the puller.  If we have another slower, thats OK, I am STILL gonna slow on inc, group's better off that way... If we have other Crowd Control, and I get a multi pull, ones getting mezzed on the way in.  I group well with enchanters but don't need them.. I change my tactics a little to try to keep them awake, I have often had them complain of boredom when I was pulling.  I noticed no mention of pulling or crowd control in your post.  You should work on those.
<br />

<br />
<blockquote><b>Quote:</b><br><span class="quote"> People don't even want the mana song much unless they run out of KEI. </span></blockquote>
<br />
Who ARE these people?  Group with smarter people.  All of our mana songs STACK with all of the clarity line and all other mana regen.  Whether they want it or not... give it to them, you are adding to the productivity of the  group unless every single member is FOM and not casting anything.
<br />

<br />
Ok what haven't we covered?  Occlussion of Sound is one.. You just got that at 55... I pull with a resist debuff followed by a slow and frequently will refresh the resist debuff in my twist until the  main slower lands theirs. Make it easier for them.. thats a big part of our functionality.. make stuff easier.  
<br />

<br />
Lulls in 3 seconds for no mana make us an excellent puller choice.  Learn to lull pull well
<br />

<br />
So theres haste, overhaste, slows, snares, mana, resist debuffs, resist buffs, crowd control, pulling, speed, and situational tools.  Yes some of these are overshadowed by other classes isometimes if they happen to be present, but others are unmatchable.
<br />

<br />
Look at the group make-up.. look for weaknesses in it... you almost certainly have a song, or a set of songs, that will fill that gap</span></td>
