				<td colspan="2"><span>Any bard mez used to interfere with chanter mez. This was changed a while back.  Pre-mezzing is  both safe, and an excellent tactic. 
<br />

<br />
Not entirely sure what happens if you mez a mob a chanter ALREADY has mezed, it may still overwrite (and then both mezes drop 18 seconds later), but I don't think so.
<br />

<br />
Pulling in LDON's is a great idea, but if you're grouping with folks higher than you, you may start running into situations where your lull won't take effect, you can't mez the mobs, you can't charm stuff, etc. My bard is 58 now and having some of the same issues... however, there's still a TON you can do, and the 60's will bring back a lot of that capability.
<br />

<br />
Even when we have chanter buffs, groups love it if I twist Cantata (mana), Overhaste, and Rizlona's Embers (LDON song that acts as a focus for nukes under level 60).  You can play with damage shields, resists, stat and atk buffs, you can be the groups' snarer, you can disarm traps in LDON, you can track.  
<br />

<br />
Good advice to get Run3, it will help prevent the &quot;selos dropped&quot; deaths. Also if you're using 49 selos (2.5 minute duration), refresh it a bit early and you will never have the problem. </span></td>
