				<td colspan="2"><span>Actually chanter mezz ovewrites our mezz, but we can then stick our mezz on top without ovewriting theirs..  It's kinda wierd, but means I can tell when the chanty has taken over mezzing my mobs.
<br />

<br />
I pre-mezz as a matter of course in many many encounters, wherever multiple pulls happen.  Makes life for the chanter much safer, if their mezz gets resisted, my mez is still holding it.   Once their mezz lands I get the 'Your Lullaby of Morrell has worn off' message and I know I can relax.  I never get complaints.  
<br />

<br />
One thing I WOULD recommend though.  Some chanters might feel that you are stepping on their toes and that you don't respect their abilities.  With a new person I will often send them a tell, saying that I am just pre-mezzing as a matter of course and that I assume they will take over.   I have never got a bad reaction and quite often a good one.  Just let em know.
<br />

<br />
Melo</span></td>
