				<td colspan="2"><span>yes, at 56th life gets rough for a bard.  our songs are not up to snuff for most mobs, but that does not make us worthless in a group.
<br />

<br />
there is so much a bard can do, and as for ppl not wanting mana song even if they have KEI they are nuts.  IIRC kei and our mana songs STACK thus they can burn though more mana and still have some left over for their job in the group.
<br />

<br />
my only real comment is to AVOID LDoN until you hit 60th.  get with your guild, at group, get in some raids and let your defense songs wow ppl, always nice to see all/most of your resists jump by 60-120points because the BARD is near...
<br />

<br />
the reason i say AVOID LDoN for now, is nothing there that will benifit you that a good xp grind group, or raid will not do BETTER.
<br />

<br />
from 54-59 LDoN suck.  plane and simple.  nothing good about them other then a few points for a win.  the xp is pathetic, the loot is not worth it for the most part.  both of those happend right before gOd was released and SoE nerfed LDoN into oblivion for the 50s.
<br />

<br />
pre-nerf i would agree that LDoN was the best thing that ever happened to EQ, but now i say avoid if unless you are not guilded or do not have a group that your can get with on a consistant basis.
<br />

<br />
if that is the case, then put up your LFG and put in your flag that you are looking for LDoN, then go swar/chant kite and solo to get your xp and levels.
<br />

<br />
getting out of the 50s is the hardest thing until you hit 64th.  those are all h3ll levels for the most part with 59th being a double h3ll level.
<br />

<br />
best of luck, and GRATE work on getting to 56th in only 2 months as a BARD, that is tough for being new to the game.</span></td>
