				<td colspan="2"><span>For what it's worth, yes, I did bring this character up from first level.  I've gotten plenty of help along the way.  A level here or there powerleveled out, some pretty good twinking from a friend of mine who has a 65 Ranger on one account and a Bazaar Trader on another.
<br />

<br />
I've read most of the guides here, a fair chunk of the forum posts, and I ask a lot of questions in game.  I want to be good at what I do.
<br />

<br />
I have the advantage of a lot of free time.  I have many many hours invested.
<br />

<br />
Up until this point, I have enjoyed myself.  I like playing a Bard.  I like having Selo, my own Invis, Track, Sense and Disarm Traps, all the tools a Bard gets.  I'm a handy critter to have on LDoNs where I almost always pull and do it well.
<br />

<br />
I must be a traitor to my class in that I don't *like* to solo.  It's dull.  It's a lot of work.  It's got great potential to get me killed at a time when I have no back up.  I *dispise* haunting the PoK begging for a rez.
<br />

<br />
I'm in a guild.  It's a Fun and Friendship type guild, and I've passed the vast majority of them in level.  A few of them have Mains in my range, but they are usually playing their Alts.  I have no steady pool of people to join me in a group.
<br />

<br />
I've hit a point where my abilities don't seem to measure up to the mobs I'm facing.  I'm not getting xp to speak of.  Sure enough, the Doldrum Levels that everyone hates.  What I want is to be in groups so I can get some decent xp and have fun doing it.
<br />

<br />
Everyone knows they want a Cleric in their group.  They will take a Druid if they can't get one.  Everyone is always happy to have some good Tankage, a Warrior or two, a Paladin, even a Shadowknight.  Someone with some nukes is always appreciated.  What does a Bard bring to the group?  At this level, not a whole lot, and nothing anyone seems impressed with.
<br />

<br />
I feel like I'm doing something wrong.  Like I'm missing the songs that will make people go &quot;Glad we had a Bard in our group.&quot;  I'd almost be happy to just stand around and sing mana if it got me group invites and people who were happy to have a Bard added to their group.
<br />

<br />
Thanks for the responses folks.</span></td>
