				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: Not sure what role I'm supposed to be filling<a name="57423"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Aug 18 04 10:08 PM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>you have a lot to bring to the group even at your level when your songs are IMHO about as out of ballance as they get until 65th or so with other classes.
<br />

<br />

<br />
you still have great mana regen, good healing for downtime and if you have a sham/nec in your group they will absolutly LOVE you for your heal/mana song that stacks with their canni/lich thus they can feed their mana more effectively and be better in the group.
<br />

<br />
you have stackable haste, you have some very nice DoTs that have great DEBUFFs so the nukers can land for more and more often with less resists.
<br />

<br />
you have a nice little (forget if its dex or agi, but i think its dex) proc that is buff/debuff.  buff for group, debuff for target.
<br />

<br />
loads of great songs that you can use.  your pulling skills atm are a bit weak due to not being able to CONTROLL overpulls like you could just 1 or 2 levels ago with charm/mez, but that is ok.  you will DIE and DIE more often now then you did in the past if you are pulling, but IIRC you also have a nice song or two to help reduce the agro you have.  keep that in your line up if you are pulling.  its great to help your tanks pull the mob(s) off your back when a pull goes bad and they will.
<br />

<br />
bards like necros are some of the most under appriciated group members in the game.  i have lost count how many times, when i used to play, that ppl would send me a tell after i left the group for what ever reason that things got REAL hard after i left with either my nec or bard.  that was partialy due to really KNOWING my class, and partialy due to the fact that those 2 classes are great support roll types in groups.
<br />

<br />
my only beef with LDoN is the xp and loot nerf for the mid to upper 50s.  for learning how to make a group go OMG how did we do so good, or OMG how did we live though that pull?  that is what a bard will do for a group both xp grind, and LDoNs.
<br />

<br />
a strong necro can do that too, but not as effectivly as a bard under ALL cicumstances.  a nec really shines vs undead, or were there is no other form of CC to be had (as long as mobs are sub 56 that is), and they make good supprice backup healers.
<br />

<br />
wish ya best of luck, sounds like you are on the right path.  keep up the questions, and keep up the hard work at becoming one of those bards that ppl will LOVE to see you log in because they KNOW once you are in their group, the xp and loot will fly faster then if you were not with them.</span></td>
