			<tr>
				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: Not sure what role I'm supposed to be filling<a name="57754"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Aug 20 04 3:20 AM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>Not much really to add except for a few minor things to repeat and ramble on about:
<br />

<br />
1)  Katta's is great at this level for any melee.  Most do not have max stats at this level, so even with a dex buff, the additional dex from this song will max it out.  Any melee with a proc on his/her weap will luv the max dex.
<br />

<br />
2)  Largo's is great for pulling (which I am sure you already use in your normal song lineup).  Snare for the tank to have time to get agro, AC debuff, and preslow on the mob so the main group slower has time to get the mob debuffed (stacks w/ Occ) and slowed.
<br />

<br />
3)  Educate your group.  Most have no idea still to this day what a bard can or can not do except at lvl 5 when we get selos and lvl 65+.  Tell your melee to watch their proc before and after you sing Katta's for example.  Chances are if you group with them again, they will request it.  Tell your group's main crowd controller and/or slower what you are doing on pulls (see #2 above).  Tell all of your casters to compare their mana bar with and without your added song.  They will request it from then on (arrrgh...hehe!) because they are regen hungry.  State plainly that adding you as a bard to the group equals less downtime, which equals more xp in the same amount of time than without you.  Believe me, the groups will eventually get their head out of their arses and start preferring you over another class.
<br />

<br />
4)  At this level, just master pulling.  It takes awhile, but a group will completely notice the xp flow difference with you in group as opposed to you not being there.  Timing the pulls to have one mob inc just as the previous one is dying will equal nonstop xp, regardless how much you get per kill.  Nothing educates a group more than when they notice the difference in speed that their xp bar fills.
<br />

<br />
5)  Try getting groups in CoDecay.  IMHO it's the best xp at this level.  If you keep the pulls flowing, it surpasses soloing (sry, not sure about aoe soloing, i only swarmed).
<br />

<br />
6)  After lvl 63 and you get Fading Memories AA (you do have rs3 plus 6aa banked, right?), life is grand!
<br />

<br />
7)  Above all else understand this phrase:  &quot;Bards do not make a group.  Bards make a group BETTER!&quot;.  Because this really can't be parsed or distinctly noticed, most don't realize this.  Hence your dilema.
<br />

<br />
Stick to the grind for now.  Play an alt so you can realize you miss your bard.  It only gets better!</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
