			<tr>
				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: Not sure what role I'm supposed to be filling<a name="58900"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Aug 25 04 7:04 AM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>Well I think bards can make a group better to the degree they make the group...<img src="/skins/default/images/emotions/emotion-1.gif" border="0" alt="Smiley" hspace="2" />
<br />
All the things are adding up, and every single one is clearly noticable in my opinion, as it can mean wipe/extended medbreak or no wipe.
<br />
The main aspect of a bard in a group (apart from the increase in power that shows in numbers, such as haste, overhaste, attack buffs, DS, stats buffs, resistances etc.) is smoothening the whole process of fighting so far that some people tend to fall asleep. This is where your most important bardic ability, the one to entertain your group with your wit and charm should keep them going. ;)
<br />
As a bard you can even keep a weak group going and going well. You can (almost) guarantee single pulls and when the last mob is on 5% health, the new mob is already in camp, mezzed debuffed, preslowed, ready to be picked by the MT for example.
<br />
Being honest, the group would be better off dps wise with getting another ranger or wizard instead of a bard (if you arent group haster). Your songs (CotM, Zek) can compensate a bit for weakening the groups dps, giving a 15% damage boost. But still a Wizard would have added more dps. 
<br />
You see the bard's job is not to give the group a huge dps boost, the job is to make everyone's stay in the group more convenient.
<br />
A group without a bard might have wiped because of a bad pull, a slow not landing, a roamer adding, a mob gating. It might habe been unefficient because wasting too much mana on spell resists, on too long fights because of a CHing mob, the casters not having enough mana regen and the list goes on. And one bard takes care of all that. 
<br />
Of course other classes could take care of some of tasks as well, but to take care of all of them you would have to assemble your group very carefully, and there would still be things the group would be missing without a bard. 
<br />
(I've got to admit that things get a lot nicer once you have reached 65 and got certain equipment AAs and songs. Fading Memories, the 60+ songs (especially 65 mezz as well as HoS) and Epic make a Bard's life a great deal easier. But even earlier on you can add a lot to every group you join.)
<br />

<br />
Just some thoughts...<img src="/skins/default/images/emotions/emotion-1.gif" border="0" alt="Smiley" hspace="2" /></span></td>
			</tr><tr>
